f. scott fitzgerald.gloss: United States author whose novels characterized the Jazz Age in the United States (1896-1940)

fsb.gloss: the internal counterintelligence agency of the Russian Federation and successor to the Soviet KGB

fsh.gloss: a gonadotropic hormone that is secreted by the anterior pituitary and stimulates growth of Graafian follicles in female mammals, and activates the cells in male mammals that form sperm
